<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. Phylogram of Diaporthe from a Maximum Likelihood analysis based on combined ITS, cal, his 3, tef 1 and tub 2. Values above the branches indicate Maximum Likelihood bootstrap (left, ML BP ≥ 50 %) and Bayesian probabilities (right, BI PP ≥ 0.90). The tree is rooted with Diaporthella corylina. Strains in current study are in blue font and the ex-type cultures are in bold font." , "Figure 5. Diaporthe ganzhouensis on unknown host (BJFC-S 1678) a the colony on PDA and conidiomata b alpha and beta conidia c conidiogenous cells and alpha conidia. Scale bars: 10 μm (b, c)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/497460" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/497465" .

